SIMPLE: provincial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Provincial
<hw>Pro*vin"cial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>provincialis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>provincial</ets>. See
<er>Province</er>, and cf. <er>Provencal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to province; constituting a province; <as>as, a
<ex>provincial</ex> government; a <ex>provincial</ex>
dialect.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exhibiting the ways or manners of a province;
characteristic of the inhabitants of a province; not cosmopolitan;
countrified; not polished; rude; hence, narrow; illiberal.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Provincial</xex> airs and graces.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to an ecclesiastical province, or
to the jurisdiction of an archbishop; not ecumenical; <as>as, a
<ex>provincial</ex> synod</as>.</def> <rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to Provence; Provencal.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With two <qex>Provincial</qex> roses on my razed shoes.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provincial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Provincial
<hw>Pro*vin"cial</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person belonging
to a province; one who is provincial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>A monastic superior, who,
under the general of his order, has the direction of all the religious
houses of the same fraternity in a given district, called a
<xex>province</xex> of the order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provincialism</ent>⟦br⟧
